@page "/privacy"
@layout MainLayout

<DocSeo Title="Privacy" Description="BlazOrbit documentation site privacy policy. No trackers, no analytics, no third-party scripts."
        Keywords="@(new[] { "privacy", "policy", "no tracking", "cookies", "GDPR" })" />

<div class="doc-content">
    <h1>Privacy</h1>

    <p>
        This documentation site is intentionally analytics-free.
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>No Google Analytics, Plausible, Fathom, Cloudflare Web Analytics, or any other tracker.</li>
        <li>No cookies set by the site itself. The only cookie that may exist is the BlazOrbit culture cookie set by the <code>BOBCultureSelector</code> on the Server-hosted variant — a same-origin, <code>HttpOnly</code> functional cookie that records your language preference. No analytics are derived from it.</li>
        <li>No third-party scripts are loaded. Every JavaScript and CSS asset ships from the same origin as this page (<code>self</code> in CSP terms).</li>
        <li>No remote fonts. Typography is bundled.</li>
        <li>No telemetry beacons from the BlazOrbit runtime. The library never phones home; the only outbound surface in any consumer app is the optional <code>/BlazOrbit/Culture/Set</code> endpoint when Server localization is opted in.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        This policy is intentional and not subject to change without an explicit announcement on the GitHub repository.
    </p>
</div>
